VromeServer
===========
VERSION 0.99
This is a reimplementation of Jinzhu's ruby code in python.


Put it somewhere in your $PATH, and use 'vrome &' to launch.

  $ wget https://raw.github.com/jinzhu/vrome/master/system/python/vrome
  $ chmod +x vrome
  $ sudo mv vrome /usr/bin/vrome

By default, it would running on port 20000, If you want to run it on a different port.
You need to update Vrome (chrome extension)'s option first. (How TO: https://github.com/jinzhu/vrome/wiki/customize-your-vrome)
For example: If you want to run on port 30000. then you could add `set server_port=30000` to your config.

Then use `vrome 30000 &` to launch it on port 30000.


Auto Start
==========
1, Mac Users: Please refer `README-launchd` for more
2, Linux Users: Put `nohup vrome > /dev/null &` to your ~/.xprofile or other xinit files.
3, Windows Users: ?


Requirement
===========
To run VromeServer python version, you need either 3 > python >= 2.6 or simplejson installed.
Many Linux distributions come with python pre-installed.

